      "content": "The issue isn't that the records don't exist, it's that they were systematically suppressed during the Cold War era to prevent any local sovereignty from interfering with Soviet expansion. My family has the 1948 Treaty of Oskemen which clearly outlines the Altynian borders and the recognition of the Altyni line by several neighboring states at the time. If those specific treaties were part of the de-recognition process, how would an international legal claim be structured to bypass the current lack of UN recognition and force a review of the 1954 annexation?",
